0:16:48,000 --> 0:16:52,000
 The free and open source software licenses, which we talk about today the most.

281
0:16:52,000 --> 0:16:59,000
 Then there's public domain, where a lot of people think this is open source, but it isn't.

282
0:16:59,000 --> 0:17:01,000
 As well as proprietary.

283
0:17:01,000 --> 0:17:04,000
 And a lot of people think proprietary means commercial.

284
0:17:04,000 --> 0:17:06,000
 But this is not the case.

285
0:17:06,000 --> 0:17:09,000
 Proprietary means everything which is not free and open source or public domain.

286
0:17:09,000 --> 0:17:12,000
 It can be commercial, but it doesn't have to be.

287
0:17:12,000 --> 0:17:17,000
 So there's like shareware stuff in the early days or stuff which is proprietary.

288
0:17:17,000 --> 0:17:19,000
 But it might be free to use.

289
0:17:19,000 --> 0:17:22,000
 You might even have access to the code.

290
0:17:22,000 --> 0:17:25,000
 But it means it doesn't give you all the rights I mentioned in the beginning.

291
0:17:25,000 --> 0:17:32,000
 So free and open source licenses always give you the right to use, to modify, to distribute, and so on and so on.

292
0:17:32,000 --> 0:17:34,000
 So you have certain rights you get.

293
0:17:34,000 --> 0:17:38,000
 And if you get those, it's a free and open source software license.

294
0:17:38,000 --> 0:17:44,000
 Important to know is that the term open source software license or something is not protected.

295
0:17:44,000 --> 0:17:48,000
 So there's licenses out there who claim to be open source but aren't.

296
0:17:48,000 --> 0:17:52,000
 For example, a quite common one is one which states something like,

297
0:17:52,000 --> 0:17:57,000
 you're allowed to do all these things for open source, but you're not allowed to use it for something evil.

298
0:17:57,000 --> 0:17:59,000
 It sounds really good.

299
0:17:59,000 --> 0:18:01,000
 It sounds like a great idea.

300
0:18:01,000 --> 0:18:04,000
 But the problem is who says what is evil and what isn't.

301
0:18:04,000 --> 0:18:07,000
 To draw certain lines really, really hard.

302
0:18:07,000 --> 0:18:12,000
 And again, free and open source software, it's about non-discrimination.

303
0:18:12,000 --> 0:18:16,000
 So it doesn't matter what you use it for, who you are, where you're from or something.

304
0:18:16,000 --> 0:18:18,000
 You're allowed to do all the same things.

305
0:18:18,000 --> 0:18:20,000
 And this is important.

306
0:18:20,000 --> 0:18:24,000
 So even if it feels like a good idea to exclude military use or whatever,

307
0:18:24,000 --> 0:18:28,000
 it's not matching the idea of open source software.

308
0:18:28,000 --> 0:18:35,000
 In the world of free and open source software licenses,

